{"id":1170,"text":"#Treatment - Dacryoadenitis - 1D80.Y\nTreatment of the disease should be under medical supervision. Treatment depends upon the onset of disease process and its aetiology. Acute dacryoadenitis: Viral dacryoadenitis: It is usually self-limiting and does not require any treatment. Bacterial dacryoadenitis: Broad spectrum antibiotics (such as cephalosporins) may be started with, awaiting culture report. Fungal dacryoadenitis: It may require anti-fungal agents. Protozoal dacryoadenitis: Specific antiamoebic may be prescribed. Chronic dacryoadenitis: In chronic dacryoadenitis, underlying systemic disease is treated, which is guided by lacrimal gland biopsy. Prognosis: Acute dacryoadenitis: Acute dacryoadenitis is self-limited mostly and therefore carries a good prognosis. Chronic dacryoadenitis: Prognosis depends upon the underlying disease and its treatment.","entities":[{"id":17129,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":13,"end_offset":27},{"id":17130,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":170,"end_offset":190},{"id":17131,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":198,"end_offset":212},{"id":17132,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":214,"end_offset":217},{"id":17135,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":402,"end_offset":423},{"id":17141,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":553,"end_offset":575},{"id":17142,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":636,"end_offset":657},{"id":17143,"label":"Medicine_E","start_offset":659,"end_offset":668},{"id":17145,"label":"Medicine_E","start_offset":765,"end_offset":774},{"id":17147,"label":"Medicine_E","start_offset":800,"end_offset":810},{"id":17133,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":278,"end_offset":302},{"id":17134,"label":"Medicine_E","start_offset":304,"end_offset":355},{"id":17137,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":425,"end_offset":428},{"id":17138,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":460,"end_offset":484},{"id":17139,"label":"Medicine_E","start_offset":486,"end_offset":506},{"id":17140,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":526,"end_offset":548},{"id":17144,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":670,"end_offset":690},{"id":17146,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":776,"end_offset":798}],"relations":[{"id":8319,"from_id":17134,"to_id":17133,"type":"prescribed_for_R"},{"id":8322,"from_id":17143,"to_id":17144,"type":"prescribed_for_R"},{"id":8320,"from_id":17139,"to_id":17138,"type":"prescribed_for_R"},{"id":8321,"from_id":17141,"to_id":17142,"type":"has_diagnosis_R"}],"Comments":[]}
{"id":1171,"text":"#Diagnosis - Dacryoadenitis - 1D80.Y\nDiagnosis is based on the clinical presentation of the patient and the supportive tests being conducted. Patient may present with: In acute dacryoadenitis: There is usually unilateral, severe pain, associated redness with pressure sensation in superotemporal region of the eye. In chronic dacryoadenitis: Unilateral or bilateral painless enlargement of the lacrimal gland, may be present over a month, in superotemporal part of the eye. Acute dacryoadenitis: Following tests may be conducted in acute dacryoadenitis: Examination of smear of discharge from the eye, Culture and sensitivity of the discharge from the eye, Blood culture. Chronic dacryoadenitis: Chronic dacryoadenitis is usually associated with chronic systemic conditions. Test may be: Lacrimal gland biopsy. ","entities":[{"id":17110,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":13,"end_offset":27},{"id":17112,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":171,"end_offset":191},{"id":17116,"label":"Symptom_E","start_offset":342,"end_offset":408},{"id":17117,"label":"Anatomy_E","start_offset":442,"end_offset":472},{"id":17118,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":474,"end_offset":494},{"id":17121,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":554,"end_offset":600},{"id":17122,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":602,"end_offset":655},{"id":17126,"label":"Complication_E","start_offset":746,"end_offset":773},{"id":17128,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":788,"end_offset":809},{"id":17111,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":108,"end_offset":124},{"id":17114,"label":"Symptom_E","start_offset":210,"end_offset":313},{"id":17115,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":318,"end_offset":340},{"id":17119,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":506,"end_offset":512},{"id":17123,"label":"Diagnosis_E","start_offset":657,"end_offset":670},{"id":17124,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":672,"end_offset":694},{"id":17125,"label":"Disease_E","start_offset":696,"end_offset":718},{"id":17127,"label":"Diagnosis_E","s